fieldNotes: Doors out of water on several occasions due to waves- small net opening. Shallow foot rope <20m

10 minutes added to set as it took 10 min to get doors fishing (Neville comment:  fishing time should not be started if doors not started and net not open-1.7m is NOT a fishing net.  Therefore, fishing start time should be 11:23 if this is case.  Should review with Alecksey for validation.).   Bongo had to be repeated due to cable tangle.
Added 200 lbs of weight in order to expand vertical opening. Initially it was 400lbs, this set-600lbs.
Headrope target surface but actual depth ~ 2 m based on RBR
to increase vertical opening an additional back side chain was attached on the foot rope (5 feet on each side= 10 feet total). It means additional 50lbs weight on gear.
Head rope collapsed down several times especially at start and end of set.
Lost float 10min into tow- headrope dove to 10m. Net was twisted
Strong tidal stream oceanward, very hard to keep trawl on surface! Headrope varied between surface 10m. Cable got caught on crane block for CTD sampling (follow up with UBC for further comments)
Shoreward tidy, hard to keep trawl on surface- had to shorten warp distance
Hauled toward Bowie seamount;  Headrope dove to 10m 3x in first 15 min ~30s each.
Headrope dip down to ~17 meters at beginning of tow.
Problem with cable on CTD- all samples 10m shallower than usual
Foot rope RBR failed- no net opening data
